sql:
SELECT state_id, year, non_problem_percentage, at_risk_percentage, problem_percentage
FROM risk_assessments
ORDER BY year DESC;

SELECT s.state_name, r.year, r.total_population
FROM states s
JOIN risk_assessments r ON s.state_id = r.state_id;

SELECT s.state_name, ra.year, ra.total_population
FROM risk_assessments ra
JOIN states s ON ra.state_id = s.state_id;

external_knowledge:
- Turbulent seas of change here refers to significant fluctuations or changes in risk assessments; 
- Problem percentages represent the share of the population deemed at risk; 
- Average fluctuation measures the typical yearly shift in these percentages.
